Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Ltd &lt;MITH.T>and Mitsui and Co Ltd &lt;MITS.T> are likely to win an order foroil-related equipment worth about 600 mln yen this week from aHungarian company trading in equipment for the chemicalindustry, sources in the industry said.    The equipment, developed by Royal Dutch/Shell Group&lt;RD.AS>, removes water from carbonic acid gas which is injectedinto oil wells to increase oil production.    The sources said the Hungarian company, Chemokomplex, hasasked the World Bank for money to buy the equipment. Hungarygets 90 pct of its crude oil from the Soviet Union. REUTER&#3;